When washing, we wipe not only the bottom and the top of our hands, but also: finger ends (connected or individually) – wipe them with circular moves with the inside of the other hand, the spaces between your fingers (swipe your hands, wiping your fingers against yourself), thumbs – each thumb includes the other hand and in such a cover we spin a moment to the right and left.
In an emergency (when you cannot wash your hands) you should wipe your hands with a wet handkerchief and then use an antibacterial gel (in drugstores, from PLN 5).
