Among the causes of the Red Paper, there is a rapid increase in urban agglomeration and global climate change.
However, the most vulnerable are those trees and bushes that occur only or mainly on our continent.
As far as typical European woodland is concerned, according to IUCN experts 58% of species are at risk and 15 percent of species, 66 species of trees and bushes, are at risk of extinction.
